<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="213" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d213">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian
                                    Pauncefote</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note, No. 518, of
                            the 13th of October last, to Viscount Gough, and to previous
                            correspondence in regard to the arrangements for preventing the use of
                            firearms in Bering Sea by pelagic sealers, I have the honor to inform
                            you that I am instructed by the Marquis of Salisbury to state that Her
                            Majesty’s Government agree to postpone further discussion on this
                            subject for the present.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Julian
                            Pauncefote.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>